column5: Good evening all,  Just wondering how you would rate the spot mentioned above?  Worth spending some time or no?  Thanks again,  MJP
Just in case BITEME hasn't seen this topic....    Burt
Caught a small trout, 15", around the area yesterday. Water is clear, but a lot of floating ice and moving leaves.
I know the ext'd season is done for, but the only luck ive had on bronte is at the harbour and in petropark (between 403/QEW & Rebecca [new st.])  I tossed a few flies north of dundas, but no luck.
